Ithink, then, that we should hold as to the pulsation of tbe beart, that the fibres ol the beart, in their contractiori, draw its cone towards its base as to the more fixed end; whence it comes about that the

walls of the ventricles are carried outwards, tbe pressure of the contained blood contributing to this.
